Beam and Spring Forces and Moments
The force in an element at any point is the force required to maintain
equilibrium if the element is cut at that point and the end 2 part of the
element is discarded.  Thus:     +ve axial forces are tensile
Forces and moments are output in element axis directions
i.e. Fx: axial force;  Fy & Fz: shear forces;  Mxx: torsion;  Myy & Mzz: moments
Element axes for springs are as defined by the spring property axis no.
For Response Spectrum analysis cases only results calculated in the analysis are available and these are only available in the axes in which they were calculated.
e.g. element displacements are only available in global directions; 2D element stresses are only available in local directions; principal stresses are not reported.
For Response Spectrum analysis cases only the sum of Total Reactions are reported.
All components are enveloped.  Components are not coexistent.
Case list:  C94 : ENV
Refer to Combination Case and Envelope Details for details of enveloping permutations.
